## 📊 Risk Scoring Guide

**Likelihood**

|Score|Level         |Meaning                     |
|-----|--------------|----------------------------|
|1    |Rare          |Unlikely to occur           |
|2    |Unlikely      |Could occur but not expected|
|3    |Possible      |Might occur at some point   |
|4    |Likely        |Will probably occur         |
|5    |Almost Certain|Expected to occur           |

**Impact**

|Score|Level     |Meaning            |
|-----|----------|-------------------|
|1    |Negligible|Minimal effect     |
|2    |Minor     |Small disruption   |
|3    |Moderate  |Noticeable impact  |
|4    |Major     |Significant damage |
|5    |Critical  |Catastrophic impact|

**Risk Score = Likelihood × Impact**

|Score|Rating    |
|-----|----------|
|1–4  |🟢 Low     |
|5–9  |🟡 Medium  |
|10–19|🟠 High    |
|20–25|🔴 Critical|

